          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-18 15:32:45" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to exclude or remove someone from an association</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to exclude</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to separate</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to get rid of</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is, of course, possible to translate ἀφορίζω in {S:04200602200020} as ‘not to welcome,’ but the emphasis of ἀφορίζω is to exclude from a relationship which has previously existed. One may therefore translate {S:04200602200020} as ‘happy are you … when people no longer welcome you in their company … because of the Son of Man.’ By introducing the temporal element ‘no longer,’ the fact of exclusion is made clear.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
